Kia ora Raffaella,

Thank you for your email and for raising your concerns.

I sincerely apologise for the inconvenience and stress this privacy request=
 has caused. We are committed to supporting you and addressing your concern=
s as best we can.

Timeframes
We acknowledge that this process has taken longer than expected, and we app=
reciate your patience. Due to current workload volumes, we kindly ask for y=
our understanding as we work towards providing the requested information by=
 8 October 2025. Our teams are working diligently to collate all relevant i=
nformation, and we remain focused on delivering the best possible outcome.

Privacy & Security
I want to reassure you that your personal information has not been exposed.=
 The shared folder was created solely for the purpose of sharing documents =
with you and does not contain any stored data. As an added security measure=
, the folder will be automatically deleted after 30 days=E2=80=94unless you=
 require access for longer. Please let us know if that=E2=80=99s the case. =
All records relevant to both claims are being preserved.

Redactions
The redactions made are currently under review. Based on our assessment so =
far, redactions have been applied for the following reasons:

  1.  Personal information of third parties (e.g. names, bank account numbe=
rs, addresses, email addresses) =E2=80=93 Section 53(b)
  2.  Personal information of staff members involved in the claim =E2=80=93=
 Section 53(b)
  3.  Commercially sensitive information (e.g. internal assessments or meth=
odologies used to reach certain outcomes) =E2=80=93 Section 53(b)  Please n=
ote: In these cases, personal information refers only to the outcome, not t=
he process used to reach it.
The final documents will include clear explanations for each redaction when=
 they are shared with you.

Fees
Under guidance from the Office of the Privacy Commissioner, Tower may charg=
e a reasonable fee if a request goes beyond the scope of a standard privacy=
 request. In this case, your request for indexing may fall into that catego=
ry.
We will not charge for the first hour, but any additional time may be charg=
ed at $30 per half hour. Please confirm whether you would still like us to =
proceed with the indexing, given the potential fee.

Thank you again for your understanding. We remain committed to providing th=
e requested information by 8 October 2025.

If you are not satisfied with our response, you may lodge a complaint with =
the Office of the Privacy Commissioner: Office of the Privacy Commissioner =
| Submit a complaint<https://www.privacy.org.nz/your-rights/making-a-compla=
int-to-the-privacy-commissioner/complaint-landing-page/?SecurityID=3D4263e8=
575b7718fb1f5bf0015055638884935eee>

Please let me know if you have any questions to the above.

Warm regards
[cid:image001.png@01DC3119.E0CA4CD0]
Johann Engelbrecht
Compliance and Privacy Advisor
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
