Kia ora team, Thank you for your email. I=E2=80=99d like to clarify a few p=
oints so we can bring this to a timely conclusion: Timeframes My Privacy Ac=
t request was made on 1 July 2025. The statutory timeframe has passed. On 1=
5 September 2025 I was told

Kia ora team,

Thank you for your email.

I=E2=80=99d like to clarify a few points so we can bring this to a timely c=
onclusion:

Timeframes
My Privacy Act request was made on 1 July 2025. The statutory timeframe has=
 passed. On 15 September 2025 I was told the additional material would be p=
rovided within 5 working days. Could you please explain why the date has no=
w moved to 8 October, and on what basis?

Privacy & security
There have been several issues to date (broken ShareFile links, visibility =
of another customer=E2=80=99s folder, and access not tied to my identity). =
I appreciate that you have notified OPC and recreated folders; however, the=
se incidents, combined with delay, have caused avoidable stress. Please con=
firm the containment steps taken and that all records relevant to both clai=
ms are being preserved.

Redactions
The material provided so far is heavily redacted without identification of =
the grounds relied upon. For every redaction or withholding, please set out=
 the specific ground and provide the least-redacted version possible.

Fees
I do not accept that a fee is appropriate in this case. No charges were men=
tioned previously, and it is Tower=E2=80=99s responsibility to maintain and=
 retrieve my claim information. If you now believe a fee is required, pleas=
e set out:


  *   the legal basis you rely on,
  *   the specific activities the fee would cover, and
  *   the total amount, and how this is  calculated and why you believe it =
is  reasonable

Delivery
Please confirm that the complete files for both claims=E2=80=94together wit=
h an index and the specific grounds for any redactions=E2=80=94will be prov=
ided by 8 October 2025, without further extension and without charge.

I remain keen to resolve this directly. If it cannot be resolved on this ba=
sis, I will consider referring the matter to the Office of the Privacy Comm=
issioner

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella del Prete

