Kia ora Privacy Team, Thanks for checking in. I can access the link; howeve=
r, it is not identity-restricted. As a test, I could open the folder using =
a different, unknown email address simply by entering a name and passing re=
CAPTCHA. I=E2=80=99ve saved
Kia ora Privacy Team,

Thanks for checking in. I can access the link; however, it is not identity-=
restricted. As a test, I could open the folder using a different, unknown e=
mail address simply by entering a name and passing reCAPTCHA. I=E2=80=99ve =
saved screenshots. Please treat this as a security issue.

For clarity, on 1 July 2025 I requested a full copy of my file for both cla=
ims (C90306048 and C90306256), =E2=80=9Cincluding all internal notes, repor=
ts, third-party correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, and any other =
material Tower holds in relation to these claims.=E2=80=9D
Legal effect: Under IPP6 Privacy Act 2020, I=E2=80=99m entitled to access m=
y personal information. =E2=80=9CIncluding=E2=80=9D is non-exhaustive, cove=
ring all formats and systems (e.g., email, IM/Teams/Slack, call recordings/=
transcripts, SMS, photos/video, test results, and native costing spreadshee=
ts). It also extends to information held for Tower by its agents/contractor=
s. If anything is withheld or redacted, please identify the specific ground=
(s).

Fair Insurance Code: As a signatory, Tower commits to handling claims and c=
omplaints honestly, fairly, transparently, and in a timely way, with clear =
communication about what you will do and when. The insecure link, incomplet=
e response, and broad redactions to date don=E2=80=99t feel consistent with=
 those commitments.

I also want to note the human impact. I=E2=80=99m already dealing with the =
aftermath of the fire; the insecure link, incomplete response, and redactio=
ns have added avoidable stress and time burden.

REQUESTS AND TIMEFRAMES

A) Security / containment =E2=80=93 by 5:00pm NZT, Thursday 25 September 20=
25


  *   Revoke/disable the current link(s) and re-issue recipient-specific ac=
cess tied solely to my email (no public link).
  *   Provide ShareFile audit logs (link creation, permissions, and all acc=
ess events: timestamp, user/email, IP, action).
  *   Confirm the containment steps taken and whether a notifiable privacy =
breach assessment was made; if notified, please provide the OPC reference n=
umber; if not, please provide your serious-harm assessment.

B) Substantive Privacy Act response =E2=80=93 by 5:00pm NZT, Thursday 25 Se=
ptember 2025

Please conduct a fresh, enterprise-wide search and provide the complete fil=
es across all systems and agents/contractors for both claims, including (no=
n-exhaustive):

  *   Claim diary/notes and task logs (full chronology).
  *   Internal communications: emails and IM (e.g., Teams/Slack).
  *   Call recordings/transcripts for all calls with me (inbound/outbound),=
 any video calls, and voicemail.
  *   SMS/texts and chat messages with me.
  *   Instructions to/from assessors and contractors, all quotes/scopes/var=
iations, and native costing files/spreadsheets used to build any scope/SOW.
  *   Site media: all photos and videos.
  *   Testing/technical reports: moisture logs; soot/smoke/odour assessment=
s; HVAC/duct contamination; asbestos sampling/clearances; electrical, gas, =
and engineering reports/results.
  *   Third-party correspondence relating to my claims.
  *   ShareFile configuration and access/audit logs for links used to provi=
de my data.

Please also provide a document index (date, author, short description, and =
system/location) so I can verify completeness. For each redaction/withholdi=
ng, identify the specific ground(s).
To assist completeness, please include a brief search methodology (systems =
searched, date ranges, search terms, and which third parties were asked to =
supply records). If any category does not exist, please state that expressl=
y.

C) Records preservation (effective immediately)

Please preserve all records relating to my claims =E2=80=94 until both clai=
ms have been fully settled and all requested documentation has been provide=
d. This includes contractor files, access logs and backups. Kindly confirm =
 that any automatic deletion settings have been paused for the relevant mai=
lboxes, systems and backups.

For reference, the current folder contains only six documents (which I have=
 consolidated in teh attached file) , which is plainly incomplete for a ful=
l file response. I=E2=80=99m keen to resolve this directly and will review =
whatever you provide promptly.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella del Prete
